content: The ideoscope and the infoscore could work in tandem, picking the right informational interventions in the form of pieces of content in order to steer the cognitive ecology of the conceptarium in the right direction.
In the view of mind as memetic ecology, the mind ceases to play an active role of generator of thought.

One could construct a memetic emulation of one's cognitive ecology through a retrieval step of finding thoughts from the conceptarium, and then with a certain probability generating a new one or moving to other saved thoughts.
Simultaneous identical inventions might be explained as outputs of convergent memetic evolution.
Systematically downplaying other perspectives is narrow-minded. Degrading terms like being programmed or brainwashed being too easily thrown around indicates memetic resistance.
If the conceptarium can be used to prime yourself before content consumption, can it be used to seed reflection sessions? Overarching themes...
In light of ideoscopic target indicators, content can also be evaluated in terms of how it's predicted to influence performance against the objectives.
An eventful memetic emulation of one's thought process can also take into account as priors for retrieval the activations of certain thoughts. In this, it can be a closer reflection of one's mind.

The conceptarium can be seen as a sample of your thought process, rather than a perfect reflection of your thought process. This more humble, modest take would make it more sustainable to talk about quantifying your thought process from ideas.
In the social realm of cognition, we are able to make use of analogies between relationships and translate dynamics.
